Internal web services here use versioned URIs, like /v1/foo.

Another approach is to change the identifier when the underlying
resource changes, but without naming it by version.  So v1 is /foo and
v2 is /bar.

Another approach is to use content negotiation, so v1 does &quot;Accept:
foo&quot; and v2 does &quot;Accept: bar&quot;.

-Lucas

